				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-466275#post-1452026</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-466275/scp-1799#post-1452026</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 17 May 2012 23:28:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DocPyro</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>444179</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>The interview is by far the worst part of the whole thing. Drop it entirely, or make it significantly longer and more subtle. One thing that might work is if the interviewer were unintentionally delivering set up lines with the subject responding involuntarily and growing gradually more horrified by it.</p> <p>I: You remind me of someone, and I've just figured out who. Emmett Kelly. But I'm probably dating myself.<br /> S: Well, no one else is going to. &lt;winces&gt; I'm sorry. I can't stop them.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
